text: Janet Benshoof (May 10, 1947 - December 18, 2017) was an American human rights activist and lawyer. She was born in Detroit Lakes, Minnesota. She was the President and Founder of the Global Justice Center. She founded the Center for Reproductive Rights, the world's first international human rights organization focused on reproductive choice and equality.\- About - Our Team. Global Justice Center. Retrieved December 16, 2017. Benshoof died of uterine cancer on December 18, 2017 in Manhattan, New York at the age of 70. ==References== Category:1947 births Category:2017 deaths Category:Deaths from uterine cancer Category:Cancer deaths in New York City Category:American human rights activists Category:Lawyers from Minnesota Category:People from Minnesota
